  "prompt": "What is the best drama (genre) movie?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" drama movie is highly subjective, as opinions on films vary greatly depending on individual tastes and preferences. However, there are several drama movies that are widely regarded as masterpieces by critics and audiences alike. Some of these include:\n\n1. **\"The Godfather\" (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola, this iconic film about the powerful Corleone crime family is often cited as one of the greatest movies ever made.\n\n2. **\"Schindler's List\" (1993)** - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this harrowing film tells the true story of Oskar Schindler, who saved over a thousand Jewish lives during the Holocaust.\n\n3. **\"Forrest Gump\" (1994)** - Directed by Robert Zemeckis, this heartwarming and epic tale follows the life of a simple man with a kind heart who witnesses and influences several historical events.\n\n4. **\"12 Angry Men\" (1957)** - Directed by Sidney Lumet, this intense courtroom drama revolves around a jury deliberating the guilt or innocence of a defendant.\n\n5. **\"Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont, this film tells the powerful story of friendship and hope within the confines of a prison.\n\n6. **\"Citizen Kane\" (1941)** - Directed by Orson Welles, this film is often hailed as one of the greatest of all time, exploring themes of power, corruption, and the American Dream.\n\nThese films are just a few examples of highly acclaimed dramas. Ultimately, the best drama movie for you will depend on your personal preferences and what themes or styles resonate most with you.",
